WHAT'S CHANGEDSouth32 Ltd (S32.AX)FromToPrice TargetA$3.45A$3.30South32 Ltd (S32.J)Price TargetZAc 3,995ZAc 3,799
We update our model for FY25 results.

Model and valuation changes: We update our model for the FY25 result, which leads to a fall in our EPS \(3.4\%\) , to \(\mathrm{US}\Phi 0.15 / \mathrm{sh}\) . We update our production, costs and capex forecasts for FY26 and FY27 guidance, lowering our FY26e/FY27e EPS \(25\% /16.3\%\) , to \(\mathrm{US}\Phi 0.19 / \mathrm{sh}\) and \(\mathrm{US}\Phi 0.24 / \mathrm{sh}\) , respectively. These EPS changes drive our base case valuation lower by 20cps, to \(\mathrm{A}\Phi 3.20 / \mathrm{sh}\) . Our bull case valuation also falls 20cps, to \(\mathrm{A}\Phi 5.05 / \mathrm{sh}\) off the lower base. Our bear case valuation rises 5cps, to A \(1.80 / \mathrm{sh}\) on lower guided near- term capex vs our previous estimates. Our probability weights for our DCF- based sum- of- the- parts valuation (20% bull, 60% base, 20% bear) are unchanged. Overall, our price target falls 15cps, to \(\mathrm{A}\Phi 3.30\mathrm{sh}\) . Our EPS and price target for S32 J) have been derived by converting our Australian price target using AUDUSD 0.65 and USDZAR 17.69.
